---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "@data/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Security model"
  description="OpenBurnBar's security stance — daemon socket auth, Keychain-scoped secrets, App Check, Apple JWS verification, ECIES cross-device credential escrow."
>
  <section class="pagehead">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--ember">Security</span>
      <h1 class="pagehead__h">A defensive product, not a hardened castle.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        OpenBurnBar is a developer tool that runs as your user. That posture
        shapes every security choice we make. Here's what we defend against,
        what we don't pretend to, and how to reach us if you find something.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="threats">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="sec-head">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--ember">Threats &amp; mitigations</span>
        <h2>The top five we actively defend.</h2>
      </header>

      <ol class="threats__list">
        <li>
          <div class="threat__num mono">01</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Local user impersonation of the daemon RPC</h3>
            <p>
              The daemon socket is a UNIX socket under your home directory with
              filesystem ACLs set to <code>0o600</code>. Every RPC requires an
              auth token; the token is passed via <code>launchd</code>
              <code>EnvironmentVariables</code>, not CLI args — keeping it out
              of <code>ps aux</code>. The plist itself is <code>0o600</code>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="threat__num mono">02</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Secrets at rest</h3>
            <p>
              Provider API keys go in the macOS Keychain with
              <code>kSecAttrAccessibleWhenUnlockedThisDeviceOnly</code>. The
              SQLCipher database key is held the same way. Equivalent risk to
              any unsandboxed app running as your user.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="threat__num mono">03</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Unauthorized cloud access</h3>
            <p>
              Firestore is gated by Firebase Auth, owner-scoped rules per
              <code>users/&#123;uid&#125;/…</code>, a secret-field-name denylist
              (<code>apiKey</code>, <code>token</code>, <code>cookie</code>,
              <code>credential</code>, …), and Firebase App Check attestation.
              <code>provider_account_secret_refs</code> is server-only — all
              client reads denied.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="threat__num mono">04</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Replayed or forged App Store entitlements</h3>
            <p>
              Every JWS receipt is verified server-side against a vendored set of
              Apple root CAs, pinned by SHA-256. The
              <code>appAccountToken</code> is a UUID bound to your Firebase UID.
              Entitlement state is re-reconciled against
              <code>getAllSubscriptionStatuses</code>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="threat__num mono">05</div>
          <div>
            <h3>Cross-device credential exposure</h3>
            <p>
              Cross-device credential transfer uses ECIES (P-256 + AES-GCM)
              escrow. Private keys never leave the device Keychain. Firestore
              only ever sees ciphertext and non-sensitive metadata.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="notpretend">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <header class="sec-head">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--ember">What we don't pretend</span>
        <h2>Known limits, on the page.</h2>
      </header>
      <ul class="notpretend__list">
        <li><strong>The macOS app is not sandboxed</strong>. Like most developer tools, it runs as your user. The security boundary is Developer ID signing + notarization + Gatekeeper, plus a defensive daemon and Keychain-scoped secrets.</li>
        <li><strong>Provider APIs are not certificate-pinned</strong>. System trust store applies. If you need vendor-side pinning, this is on the candidate list.</li>
        <li><strong>The optional Cursor connector tunnel</strong> routes BYOK traffic through Cloudflare when you turn it on. This is the only way today to land Cursor BYOK on a localhost endpoint.</li>
        <li><strong>iCloud uses your Apple ID</strong>, not our infrastructure. Conflict copies can happen; that is iCloud's behavior.</li>
        <li><strong>App Check enforcement is checked at launch-time and operationally</strong>, not at every request from a runtime probe. The commercial-launch gate enforces it before publishing.</li>
        <li><strong>Sentry diagnostics</strong> (opt-in) anonymizes the user ID via a hash seeded from the bundle ID and full user name. Not direct PII, but worth knowing.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="releasechain">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="sec-head">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--ember">Releases</span>
        <h2>Provenance you can verify.</h2>
      </header>
      <ul class="releasechain__list">
        <li><strong>Signed and notarized</strong> with a Developer ID, stapled. <code>spctl</code> verifies on Gatekeeper-enabled Macs.</li>
        <li><strong>SHA-256 and SHA-512 checksums</strong> are published next to each release artifact.</li>
        <li><strong>Optional GPG-signed checksum file</strong> for stronger chain of trust.</li>
        <li><strong>SPDX SBOM</strong> per release.</li>
        <li><strong>Release-metadata JSON</strong> with build commit, build date, and verified artifact hashes.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="report">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <header class="sec-head">
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--ember">Reporting</span>
        <h2>If you find something, tell us.</h2>
      </header>
      <p class="lead">
        Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.privacyContact}`}>{SITE.privacyContact}</a> with a description of the issue.
        Please don't open public GitHub issues for active vulnerabilities — give us a chance to fix them first.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        See the full <a href={`${SITE.github}/blob/main/SECURITY.md`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SECURITY.md</a>
        for the canonical disclosure policy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pagehead { padding-block: var(--s-9) var(--s-6); }
  .pagehead__h { margin-top: var(--s-3); max-width: 22ch; }
  .pagehead .lead { margin-top: var(--s-4); max-width: 60ch; }
  .sec-head { display: grid; gap: var(--s-3); margin-bottom: var(--s-6); max-width: 64ch; }

  .threats { padding-block: var(--s-9); border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line); }
  .threats__list { display: grid; gap: var(--s-5); }
  .threats__list li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 60px minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: var(--s-5);
    padding-bottom: var(--s-5);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink-line-soft);
  }
  .threats__list li > div { min-width: 0; }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .threats__list li { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr); gap: var(--s-2); }
  }
  .threats__list li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .threat__num {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--ember-bright);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .threats__list h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--text-bright);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 36, "wght" 540;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
  }
  .threats__list p { color: var(--text-base); }
  .notpretend, .releasechain, .report {
    padding-block: var(--s-9);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
  }
  .notpretend__list, .releasechain__list { display: grid; gap: var(--s-3); }
  .notpretend__list li, .releasechain__list li {
    color: var(--text-base);
    padding-left: 1.1em;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .notpretend__list li::before, .releasechain__list li::before {
    content: "—";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--ember-bright);
  }
  .notpretend__list strong, .releasechain__list strong { color: var(--text-bright); }
  .report a { color: var(--ember-bright); text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
